result.formatted_address: Hong Kong, Discovery Bay, Cafe Deck, 地下 G08A 號 舖
result.name: Coyote Mexican Cantina

reviews.text: Good food, but not “great” enough to deserve a fifth star. I would definitely recommend it. Prices were as you would expect here. This whole area is quite lively and exciting which I loved. Staff was friendly and had our table set aside as our reservation requested.

Went there for dinner; tried the burrito and enchiladas; large portions, served with rice, salsa and chilli. Thought they were quite good. The Bloody Maria was bloody awful though, with just too much crushed black pepper; they were quick to change it but unfortunately it couldn’t be rescued. Other than that, a pleasant experience. Staff are cheerful and attentive and ambiance was quite nice, though we were limited to the covered areas by the rains playing spoilsport. Prices are in keeping with the general standard of all places in DB, so wasn’t a surprise. Mains for 3 with  two drinks came to about $800.

Decent.  The enchilada sauce was too sweet, but overall food was good.  The kids Mac n cheese was a hit.  The taco salad was so-so, not much in it.  Not quite the good Mexican food we were looking for.

Almost didn't go here based on some of the reviews, but I'm ultimately glad we did. We popped in on a Thursday when they had their buffet. Like everything in Discovery Bay, it's expensive, but all four of is enjoyed our meal. The queso was great, the quesadillas were good, and the fajitas also hit the spot. Oh, and washing it down with Dos Equis Amber was nice too.
Nice Mexican restaurant, lunch set special with reasonable price. Every Thursday night has all you can eat promotion.

result.name: Discovery Bay Plaza

reviews.text: Nice place with good food and places to shop, would say it needs a fresh coat of paint (but where doesn't in Hong Kong with the humidity). The ferry (runs to Central) is easy to get to and runs I think every 30 minutes. Is you get a chance to go to the Korean place where you grill your own food, you must, fantastic food.
Great place overlooking the beach and close to ferry

Major commercial centre for Discovery Bay residents. Banks, supermarket, salon, department and grocery stores intend for maximum convenience. Residents and tourists never need to worry about food as there are numerous cuisine choices: Italian, Middle East, Mexican, BBQ, Chinese, bars and pubs. Fairs are also held for festival celebrations. Unfortunately the bus terminal and part of the shopping mall is under expansion which is expected to complete in 2019. Nevertheless old needs to go for new to come!  Look forward to the new look of DB Plaza!
Nice plaza and square. Plenty of restaurants with outdoor seating and some shops as well.
Europe style. A completely different feel, very relaxed.
